    <text>
        <body>
           <div type="edition" subtype="ogham" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="pgl" resp="#NW">
            <ab>
                    <lb n="1" style="text-direction:up-top-down"/><persName><name nymRef="#ercagnas">ᚓᚏᚉᚐᚌᚅᚔ</name> <name nymRef="#maqqas-erciās" type="binomial"><w lemma="maqqas">ᚋᚐᚊ<supplied reason="lost">ᚔ</supplied></w><name nymRef="#ercias">ᚓ<supplied reason="lost">ᚏ</supplied>ᚉᚔᚐᚄ</name></name></persName>
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="edition" subtype="transliteration" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="pgl" resp="#NW">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1" style="text-direction:up-top-down"/><persName><name nymRef="#ercagnas" type="binomial">ERCAGNI</name> <name nymRef="#maqqas-erciās" type="binomial"><w lemma="maqqas">MAQ<supplied reason="lost">I</supplied></w><name>E<supplied reason="lost">R</supplied>CIAS</name></name></persName>
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <p></p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation">
                <p>‘of Ercán (son) of Mac-Ercae’</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>MAQI-ERCIAS is probably a single binomial name, corresponding to OIr. <distinct xml:lang="sga">Mac-Ercae</distinct> ‘son/devotee of Erc’, rather than MAQI ERCIAS with the word for son seperate (McManus 2004, 18). This binomial name, as well as the simplex basis *erko/ā-, are very common in ogham inscriptions from southern Ireland: MAQI-ERCIAS (I-COR-077 = CIIC 125; Rooves More, Co. Cork); MAQI ERCA (I-KER-037 = CIIC 169; Ballyeightragh, Co. Kerry); MAQI-ERCCIA (I-KER-043 = CIIC 175; Burnham West, Co. Kerry); ERC MAQI MAQI-ERCIAS (I-KER-046 = CIIC 178; Coumeenoole North, Co. Kerry); M[AQ]I-[E]RCIA (I-KER-074 = CIIC 205; Derryquin, Co. Kerry), [MAQ]I-ERACIAS (I-KIK-007 = CIIC 32; Gowran, Co. Kilkenny). Although the inscription commemorates a man, ERCIAS has a feminine ending and was possibly the name of a female, mythical, eponymous ancestor.</p>
            </div>
